-- Chrysler says October sales up 37 percent
-- 
-- Wed Nov 3, 2010 11:51am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/11/03/us-autos-chrysler-idUSTRE6A253020101103

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - Chrysler, managed by Fiat ( FIA.MI ), said on Wednesday its sales in the United States rose 37 percent in October. 

 Highlights: * Says October U.S. sales up 37 percent. * Says October U.S. represent 7th consecutive month of year-on-year increase. * Says ended October with 74 days supply of inventory at 245,739 units. * Says U.S. industry sales for October projected at 12.4 million on annualized basis.